# BookSharez Environment Variables
#
# ARCHITECTURE NOTE (June 12, 2026): BookSharez is a vanilla HTML/CSS/JS site,
# NOT a Next.js app. There is no build step and no `.env.local` bundled into a
# client. Variables fall into two groups:
#
#   1. BROWSER-SAFE (public) values — the Supabase project URL and the
#      publishable/anon key — live directly in js/supabase-config.js. They are
#      safe to ship because Row Level Security protects the data. They are NOT
#      read from this file.
#
#   2. SECRETS (service-role key, ISBNdb, Google Books, AI keys) must NEVER
#      reach the browser. They are set as Supabase Edge Function secrets via the
#      Supabase dashboard or CLI (`supabase secrets set NAME=value`), and are
#      only readable from inside Edge Functions (Deno.env.get('NAME')).
#
# This file is a REFERENCE of every secret the project expects by phase. Do not
# commit real values. (No `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` prefixes — that was a Next.js
# convention and no longer applies.)

# ============================================
# SUPABASE (Required - Phase 1)
# ============================================
# Get these from: https://app.supabase.com/project/_/settings/api
#
# Browser-safe (already in js/supabase-config.js, listed here for reference):
#   SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxx.supabase.co
#   SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_supabase_publishable_anon_key_here
#
# Secret — Edge Function only (supabase secrets set):
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key_here

# ============================================
# ISBN LOOKUP APIs (Required - Phase 1)
# ============================================
# All of these are Edge Function secrets — never placed in client JS.
#
# ISBNdb (Primary): https://isbndb.com/apidocs/v2
# Basic plan: 1 request/second (api2.isbndb.com), 7-day trial
ISBNDB_API_KEY=your_isbndb_api_key_here

# Google Books API (Fallback): https://console.cloud.google.com
# Free tier: 1000 requests/day
GOOGLE_BOOKS_API_KEY=your_google_books_api_key_here

# ============================================
# AI PRICING (Required - Phase 1)
# ============================================
# Edge Function secret. Choose ONE provider:

# Option 1: Anthropic Claude (recommended)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_anthropic_api_key_here

# Option 2: OpenAI
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# ============================================
# PAYMENT PROCESSING (Phase 3)
# ============================================
# Stripe: https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=your_stripe_secret_key_here          (Edge Function secret)
# STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_stripe_publishable_key_here (browser-safe)
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_stripe_webhook_secret_here   (Edge Function secret)

# ============================================
# SHIPPING (Phase 3)
# ============================================
# EasyPost: https://www.easypost.com/account/api-keys
# EASYPOST_API_KEY=your_easypost_api_key_here

# Shippo (Alternative): https://goshippo.com/docs/
# SHIPPO_API_KEY=your_shippo_api_key_here

# ============================================
# EMAIL (Phase 3)
# ============================================
# Resend: https://resend.com/api-keys
# RESEND_API_KEY=your_resend_api_key_here

# ============================================
# MONITORING (Optional)
# ============================================
# Sentry: https://sentry.io/settings/account/api/auth-tokens/
# SENTRY_DSN=your_sentry_dsn_here              (browser-safe)
# SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN=your_sentry_auth_token_here (Edge Function secret)

# ============================================
# DEVELOPMENT (Optional)
# ============================================
# Static site is served locally with any static server (e.g. `npx serve`).
# These limits are enforced in client JS and/or Edge Functions, not a framework.

# Rate limiting (requests per hour) — enforced server-side in Edge Functions
RATE_LIMIT_MAX=100

# File upload limits (bytes)
MAX_FILE_SIZE=5242880
